medium_description_en: Classifies severity of adverse events after neurosurgery.

seo.meta_description_en: The Therapy-Disability-Neurology (TDN) Grade classifies severity of adverse events after neurosurgery.
seo.keywords_en: Therapy-Disability-Neurology (TDN) Grade, TDN grade, therapy, disability, neurology, therapy disability neurology grade, neurosurgery, adverse events

how_to_use.use_case_en: Do you use the Therapy-Disability-Neurology (TDN) Grade and want to contribute your expertise? Join our contributor team!

next_steps.advice_en: Do you use the Therapy-Disability-Neurology (TDN) Grade and want to contribute your expertise? Join our contributor team!

Original/Primary Reference.text: Terrapon APR, Zattra CM, Voglis S, et al. Adverse events in neurosurgery: the novel therapy-disability-neurology grade. Neurosurgery. 2021;89(2):236-245.

Other References.text: Gómez Vecchio T, Corell A, Buvarp D, Rydén I, Smits A, Jakola AS. Classification of adverse events following surgery in patients with diffuse lower-grade gliomas. Front Oncol. 2021;11:792878.

creator_info.about_en: Alexis P. R. Terrapon, MD, was affiliated with the University Hospital of Zürich and the Cantonal Hospital of St.Gallen in Switzerland at the time of publication of the TDN grade. Dr. Terrapon's primary research is focused on outcome research in neurosurgery, functional neurosurgery, and neuro-oncology.

input_schema.name: therapy
input_schema.tips_en: *Allowed therapeutic modalities are antiemetics, antipyretics, analgesics, diuretics, electrolytes, and bedside opening of wound infections.

options.label: Not requiring any treatment or intervention other than those allowed*
Requiring pharmacological treatment, blood transfusion or total parenteral nutrition
Requiring surgical, endoscopic, or radiologic intervention
Life-threatening and requiring management in intensive care

input_schema.label_en: Is the adverse event hindering at least one activity of daily living?
input_schema.name: d1

input_schema.label_en: Is the adverse event hindering walking, preventing the patient from attending their own bodily needs?
input_schema.name: d2

input_schema.label_en: Is the adverse event leaving the patient bedridden, in need of constant help, incontinent?
input_schema.name: d3

input_schema.label_en: Is the adverse event resulting in any new neurological deficit?
input_schema.name: neuro
